text.tspan: What is The tube
The Tube
” is a mechanism to share repositories with your team without a central server.
Think of it as a “tunnel” through the internet that lets you push/pull branches with your team.
It is like a “ad-hoc VPN” set up only for Plastic SCM.
Privacy is guaranteed since your repositories will be never published online. Repositories stay on your computer and the “
tube
” let’s your team mates push or pull
from them.
Repositories are only available when your Plastic server is connected to the tube.
You don’t need to tweak your router configuration or open any ports, just connect to
The Tube
Configure your access to The Tube
All you need to do is to enter your login information to www.plasticscm.com. If you signed up using a Google, Facebook, Twitter
or Yahoo account, then you’ll need to create a password first.
